id=acc
domain=vr25
name=Advanced Charging Controller (ACC)
version=v2025.5.18-dev-fix8
versionCode=202505182
author=VR25 (community fix8)
description=[community fix8: + fail-safe on malformed pause/resume config and recovery from a locked charging switch that stops working. fix7: Pixel/Tensor cap now HOLDS at the limit. Drives the google charge_stop_level node to pause_capacity so the firmware holds the battery flat at the cap (tight, no overshoot, true idle) instead of toggling 100/5 and sawtoothing past it; switch scanner prefers idle/flat-hold switches; restores retry-on-stall (no daemon re-init mid-pause). Includes fix2-fix6.] Extend your battery's service life by controlling charging current, temperature, and voltage. Any root solution is supported. The installation is always "systemless". Works on Android and KaiOS.
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/VR-25/acc/master/module.json
